The `IsSome` inductive type only has one constructor `of_some` which applies to `some a` values. Since `none` cannot be constructed by `of_some`, any assumption that `IsSome none` leads to a contradiction.

The proof can be done by introducing the hypothesis and then using `cases` or `nomatch` to derive a contradiction, since there's no way to construct `IsSome none`.

